window.__QUIZ_SUBJECT__=[{"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>1>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT~~MEETINGS : PURPOSE", "question": "Answer five questions in all. Question 1 and any other four questions.  Read the case below carefully and answer this question    PROBLEMS CAUSED BY THE MANAGING DIRECTOR OF OKF LIMITED  OKF limited, an initially fast growing company, was established twelve years ago to deal in office machines. The vision of the Managing Director, Dr. Rock Bansco was that the Company would become the leading supplier of office machines. He also hoped that the company would provide employment for many secondary school leavers.  Within the first five years of the company's inception, its profit grew rapidly. The customers increased so much that by the sixth year of the company's operation, the staff strength had become more than one hundred. However, all the workers who were employed in its sixth year of operation were both unqualified and inexperienced, worse still, they were given supervisory positions because of their relationship to the Managing Director in one way or the other.    As a large company, OKF Limited had six Heads of Department. However, the Managing Director hardly involved any of them in the day-to-day running of the company. He did all recruitment, purchases as well as salaries and wages administration. Staff salaries and wages were also very poor. As time went on, virtually all the staff became unhappy and this affected their morale.    The Managing Director recently called an emergency meeting to address the staff, surprisingly, he did not appoint anyone to record the proceedings of the meeting.    State two problems in OKF Limited.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Inexperience workers or staff.  - Lack of delegation of duties.", "marks": "4", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>1>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "Answer five questions in all. Question 1 and any other four questions.  Read the case below carefully and answer this question    PROBLEMS CAUSED BY THE MANAGING DIRECTOR OF OKF LIMITED  OKF limited, an initially fast growing company, was established twelve years ago to deal in office machines. The vision of the Managing Director, Dr. Rock Bansco was that the Company would become the leading supplier of office machines. He also hoped that the company would provide employment for many secondary school leavers.  Within the first five years of the company's inception, its profit grew rapidly. The customers increased so much that by the sixth year of the company's operation, the staff strength had become more than one hundred. However, all the workers who were employed in its sixth year of operation were both unqualified and inexperienced, worse still, they were given supervisory positions because of their relationship to the Managing Director in one way or the other.    As a large company, OKF Limited had six Heads of Department. However, the Managing Director hardly involved any of them in the day-to-day running of the company. He did all recruitment, purchases as well as salaries and wages administration. Staff salaries and wages were also very poor. As time went on, virtually all the staff became unhappy and this affected their morale.    The Managing Director recently called an emergency meeting to address the staff, surprisingly, he did not appoint anyone to record the proceedings of the meeting.  Outline departments in OKF Limited that should be responsible for the following activities:  - recruitment of workers  - sales promotion  - acquisition of machines  - payments", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "-  Recruitment of workers is done by personnel department.  - Sales promotion is carried out by sales and marketing department  - Acquisition of machines: Purchasing department  - Payments: Finance department/Account department.", "marks": "8", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>1>c>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "MEETINGS : DEFINITION OF MEETING", "question": "When is an emergency meeting called by the management of an organisation?", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "When there is urgent need to discuss and act prompt on some issues affecting the organisation.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>1>c>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "MEETINGS : ROLES OF THE CHAIRMAN/SECRETARY", "question": "What is the meeting's related title of the officer who should have recorded the meeting proceedings?", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "The Secretary is the officer who should have recorded the meeting proceedings.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>1>c>iii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "MEETINGS : ROLES OF THE CHAIRMAN/SECRETARY", "question": "State two duties the officer in 1(c)(ii) should have carried out before the day of the meeting.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- He prepared the agenda with the help of the chairman.  - He prepares and sends the notice of meeting to members.  - He circulates documents needed for the meeting.  - He receives apologies from members who are not able to attend the meeting.  - He prepares the chairman's agenda.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>1>c>iv", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iv", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "MEETINGS : WRITING THE MINUTES", "question": "List five headings under which the officer would have recorded the proceedings of the meeting.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Heading  - Participants  - Approval of previous minutes  - Action items  - Announcement  - Next meeting  - Adjournment  - Signature line", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>a>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE DOCUMENTS : MEANING OF OFFICE DOCUMENT", "question": "Explain this office document: Delivery note.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Delivery note: This is a document sent by the seller to the buyer for signature when goods are delivered to him and it will serve as evidence that delivery has been made. It is used when goods are transported by the seller's means of transportation.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>a>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE DOCUMENTS : MEANING OF OFFICE DOCUMENT", "question": "Explain this office document: Receipt.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Receipt: This is an acknowledgement of money received from the buyer by the seller. It is a document which confirms that payment has been made. It is prepared by the seller and sent to the buyer stating the total amount received. It is an evidence of payment.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>a>iii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE DOCUMENTS : MEANING OF OFFICE DOCUMENT", "question": "Explain this office document: Bin card.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Bin Card: This shows the record of receipts and issues of materials in the store. It is kept by the store keeper to record entries balance of stock at a particular time.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>a>iv", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iv", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE DOCUMENTS : MEANING OF OFFICE DOCUMENT", "question": "Explain this office document: Quotation.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Quotation: This is the supplier's reply to the letter of enquiry which states the price, terms of payment, delivery dates and any discount. It is a statement of price given to a buyer when he asks his supplier for quotation.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>b>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE EQUIPMENT : TYPES OF OFFICE EQUIPMENT", "question": "Identify the types of equipment which would be used to perform this task in an office    attaching a cheque to a letter to be sent to suppliers.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Stapling machine", "marks": "1", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>b>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE EQUIPMENT : TYPES OF OFFICE EQUIPMENT", "question": "Identify the types of equipment which would be used to perform this task in an office  boring holes on letters received in the registry for filing.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Perforating machine", "marks": "1", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>b>iii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE EQUIPMENT : TYPES OF OFFICE EQUIPMENT", "question": "Identify the types of equipment which would be used to perform this task in an office  getting a carbon copy of a query letter to a worker.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Carbon paper.", "marks": "1", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>b>iv", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iv", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE EQUIPMENT : TYPES OF OFFICE EQUIPMENT", "question": "Identify the types of equipment which would be used to perform this task in an office  sending an exact copy of a document to an overseas partner.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Fax machine.", "marks": "1", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>b>v", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "v", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE EQUIPMENT : TYPES OF OFFICE EQUIPMENT", "question": "Identify the types of equipment which would be used to perform this task in an office  making more copies of minutes of a meeting.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Photocopy machine.", "marks": "1", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>b>vi", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "vi", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE EQUIPMENT : TYPES OF OFFICE EQUIPMENT", "question": "Identify the types of equipment which would be used to perform this task in an office  disposing of unwanted documents.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Shredding machine.", "marks": "1", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>c>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "MAILS : TYPES OF MAILS", "question": "Explain this type of mail:    personal.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Personal mails: These are mails addressed to particular individual. They are normally opened by the person to whom they are addressed.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>c>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "MAILS : TYPES OF MAILS", "question": "Explain this type of mail:  confidential.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Confidential mails: These are mails shared with only a few people for furthering certain purposes, it is a mail that people should not have access to . It is always sealed and stamped.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>2>c>iii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "MAILS : TYPES OF MAILS", "question": "Explain this type of mail:  urgent.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Urgent mail: This type of mail require prompt attention. Once a mail is marked 'urgent', it should be attended to first before others. The contents should be checked immediately to facilitate speedy action.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>3>a>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "INFORMATION : DEFINITIONS", "question": "What us information?", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "This consists of data which has been recorded, organised, classified and processed into useful and meaningful form. It can be viewed as already processed data into the form which is meaningful to the recipient in order to enable them take decisions or actions.", "marks": "1", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>3>a>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "INFORMATION : USES", "question": "List four uses of information in an office.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Achievement of organisational objectives  - Improvement of customer relation.  - Increased profit.  - Improvement on working environment.  - Accurate forecasting  - Useful for planning and decision making", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>3>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "REPORT WRITINGS : IMPORTANCE OF REPORT WRITING", "question": "State five importance of a report.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Basis for decision making   - Provision of concrete evidence  - Enhances an organisation's image  - Increases the probability of success in an organisation  - Availability of valuable conclusions and suggestions  - Provisions of information on diverse are of human endeavour  - Provision of technical information on specialised fields.", "marks": "10", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>3>c", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "c", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "REPORT WRITINGS : TYPES", "question": "What is the difference between a statutory report and a routine report?", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Statutory report: This is a report that a company or organisation must make by law. It is mandatory submission of financial and non-financial information to a government agency while Routine report is report written for management about a project at some specified time. It is written periodically e.g daily, weekly e.t.c", "marks": "7", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>4>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "", "topic": "MEETINGS : WRITING THE MINUTES", "question": "As a Secretary of the Secretarial Students Association, write a notice of meeting to invite members to a meeting to be held in three weeks time.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Specimen 1  Queens College  Sabo-Yaba road.  Lagos.  Notice of meeting  A meeting of Secretarial Students Association is hereby given that the 4th general meeting will take place at the school premises by 3pm on thursday 30th Nov., 2018 to discuss the following issues;  (i) End of the year party of the association.  (ii) donations regarding building of structure in the school by members  (iii) delebration on how much to contribute by each member.  A.A Lawal  Secretary.    Specimen 2  Queens College  Sabo-yaba Road.  Lagos  Notice of meeting to members  Date: 30th Nov., 2018.  From: Secretary  To: All members  Subject: Annual end of the year party and building of structure in the school.  References: 16/10  A meeting of Secretarial Students Association for the month of November will take place on the 30th of November at the school auditorium.  Thank you.    A.A Lawal  Secretary.", "marks": "10", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>4>b>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "COMMUNICATION : METHODS/MEDIA OF COMMUNICATION", "question": "Explain this media of communication:    print.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Print media is the printed version of telling the news, primarily through newspapers and magazines. Before the invention and widespread use of printing presses, printed materials had to be written by hand.", "marks": "3", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>4>b>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "COMMUNICATION : METHODS/MEDIA OF COMMUNICATION", "question": "Explain this media of communication:  electronic.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Electronic media is media that uses electromechanical device to access the content broadcast or storage media that take advantage of electronic technology. They may include television, radio, internet, fax, C.D-ROMs, DVD and other medium that requires electricity or digital encoding of information.", "marks": "3", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>4>c", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "c", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "FILING : SYSTEMS OF FILING", "question": "Identify and explain four attributes of good filing system.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Security: A good filing system should ensure safety and security of all documents.    - Accessibility: The filing system should ensure that documents are easily accessible by users when they are needed.    - Simplicity: A good filing system should be simple to understand and operate. It must not be too difficult to operate.    - Economical: The best system should be the most economical to the organisation. Filing system should be economical to install and operate.", "marks": "4", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>5>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "State five functions of Finance Department in an organization.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Keeping of financial record of the organisation.  - Controlling of expenditure of the organisation.  - Dealing with tax matters of the organisation.  - Managing of financial resources of the organisation.  - Preparing of personnel cost of the organisation.  - Recording of organisation's revenue.  - Auditing records of the organisation.", "marks": "10", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>5>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "COMMUNICATION : IMPORTANCE", "question": "State five importance of communication in an organization.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Quick dissemination of Information.  - Facilities payment for goods and services.  - Advertisement of goods and services.  - Facilitates international or foreign trade.  - Risk and Cost reduction.  - Ensuring close contact between business men  - Improvement of trade.  - It ensures quick delivery of documents.", "marks": "10", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>6>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "MEETINGS : MEETING TERMINOLOGIES", "question": "Differentiate between adjournment and postponement.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Adjournment: This means to hold a meeting over until a later date. When the motion for an adjournment is moved, all deliberation stops while postponement means when a meeting is shifted from a particular date to another. It is the act of putting off a meeting to another date.", "marks": "5", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>6>b>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "THE OFFICE : LAYOUT OF AN OFFICE", "question": "What is office layout?", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "It is the practice of calculating the required office space and detailing the use of the total area available in order to ensure the practical arrangement of furniture and equipment for proper utilization of space. It is the same as office set-up.", "marks": "4", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>6>b>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "THE OFFICE : LAYOUT OF AN OFFICE", "question": "State three benefits of open office layout.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- It increases staff morale  - Economy in the use of space  - Free flow of work  - Cost minimization  - increasing productivity.", "marks": "3", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>6>b>iii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "THE OFFICE : PRINCIPLES OF OFFICE", "question": "State four factors to be considered before locating an office.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Cost of construction  - Accessibility by workers and customers  - Security  - Space  - Customer's convenience  - Possibility of future expansion.", "marks": "8", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2019>7>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2019", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE EQUIPMENT : MEANING OF OFFICE EQUIPMENT", "question": "As the purchasing officer of a service provider firm planning to purchase office equipment, state four factors you would consider in purchasing the equipment.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Space to accomodate the equipment  - Training requirement  - Staff support  - Lifespan of the equipment  - Cost of acquisition and installation  - Availability of spare parts  - Investment options.", "marks": "20", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>1>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "OVERCOMING THE CHALLENGES AT THEOLAS INTERNATIONAL COMPANY   Prior to Mr.Okonkwo's employment as the Human Resource Manager of Theolas International Company, the organization was faced with the problem of absenteeism by its workers. They came late to work and left before the closing time. As a result of this, the volume of production of the company reduced. This inturn, reduced the income of the organization so much that payments of workers' wages and salaries became difficult. Many experienced workers began to leave the firm for greener pastures.     The firm also found it difficult to meet its financial obligations to suppliers. On assumption of duty, Mr. Okonkwo quickly swung into action. He carried out an investigation to ascertain the causes of these problems. One of his findings was that workers bitterly complained about their conditions of service. Although their wages and salaries were acceptable, they asked for other benefits from the company which were denied them     Mr. Okonkwo also discovered that workers were employed without following due process. Finally, he found out that no measure was put in place to regulate the punctuality of workers. Armed with these finding, Mr Okonkwo addressed each of the issues and put in place adequate measures to ensure proper supervision and satisfaction of workers.    - Suggest one measure that Mr. Okonkwo could use to improve staff regularity at work", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Mr Okonkwo should put up a measure that would regulate the punctuality of workers after the company fulfills its own obligation.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>1>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "OVERCOMING THE CHALLENGES AT THEOLAS INTERNATIONAL COMPANY   Prior to Mr.Okonkwo's employment as the Human Resource Manager of Theolas International Company, the organization was faced with the problem of absenteeism by its workers. They came late to work and left before the closing time. As a result of this, the volume of production of the company reduced. This inturn, reduced the income of the organization so much that payments of workers' wages and salaries became difficult. Many experienced workers began to leave the firm for greener pastures.     The firm also found it difficult to meet its financial obligations to suppliers. On assumption of duty, Mr. Okonkwo quickly swung into action. He carried out an investigation to ascertain the causes of these problems. One of his findings was that workers bitterly complained about their conditions of service. Although their wages and salaries were acceptable, they asked for other benefits from the company which were denied them     Mr. Okonkwo also discovered that workers were employed without following due process. Finally, he found out that no measure was put in place to regulate the punctuality of workers. Armed with these finding, Mr Okonkwo addressed each of the issues and put in place adequate measures to ensure proper supervision and satisfaction of workers.   - Apart from irregularity at work, state two other problems in Theolas International Company", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "-The volume of production of the company reduced which led to the reduction of the organisation's income which as well made it difficult to pay worker's salaries and wages.     -The firm also found it difficult to meet its financial obligations to suppliers.", "marks": "4", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>1>c", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "c", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "OVERCOMING THE CHALLENGES AT THEOLAS INTERNATIONAL COMPANY   Prior to Mr.Okonkwo's employment as the Human Resource Manager of Theolas International Company, the organization was faced with the problem of absenteeism by its workers. They came late to work and left before the closing time. As a result of this, the volume of production of the company reduced. This inturn, reduced the income of the organization so much that payments of workers' wages and salaries became difficult. Many experienced workers began to leave the firm for greener pastures.     The firm also found it difficult to meet its financial obligations to suppliers. On assumption of duty, Mr. Okonkwo quickly swung into action. He carried out an investigation to ascertain the causes of these problems. One of his findings was that workers bitterly complained about their conditions of service. Although their wages and salaries were acceptable, they asked for other benefits from the company which were denied them     Mr. Okonkwo also discovered that workers were employed without following due process. Finally, he found out that no measure was put in place to regulate the punctuality of workers. Armed with these finding, Mr Okonkwo addressed each of the issues and put in place adequate measures to ensure proper supervision and satisfaction of workers.   - List six welfare packages that would improve workers satisfaction at Theolas International Company", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Reward the workers   - Recognize the workers   - Training and investment   - Compensation   - Drive communication and transparency   - Promote good health   - Allow employees to shape their own roles   - Correct planning of employee's schedules", "marks": "6", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>1>d", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "d", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "OVERCOMING THE CHALLENGES AT THEOLAS INTERNATIONAL COMPANY   Prior to Mr.Okonkwo's employment as the Human Resource Manager of Theolas International Company, the organization was faced with the problem of absenteeism by its workers. They came late to work and left before the closing time. As a result of this, the volume of production of the company reduced. This inturn, reduced the income of the organization so much that payments of workers' wages and salaries became difficult. Many experienced workers began to leave the firm for greener pastures.     The firm also found it difficult to meet its financial obligations to suppliers. On assumption of duty, Mr. Okonkwo quickly swung into action. He carried out an investigation to ascertain the causes of these problems. One of his findings was that workers bitterly complained about their conditions of service. Although their wages and salaries were acceptable, they asked for other benefits from the company which were denied them     Mr. Okonkwo also discovered that workers were employed without following due process. Finally, he found out that no measure was put in place to regulate the punctuality of workers. Armed with these finding, Mr Okonkwo addressed each of the issues and put in place adequate measures to ensure proper supervision and satisfaction of workers.   - State four pre-employment activities the company should have carried out in recruiting its staff", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- identify the hring need   - Devise a recruitment plan   - Write a job description   - Adertise the position   - Recruit the position   - Review applications   - Screening   - Interviews", "marks": "8", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>2>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "THE OFFICE : PRINCIPLES OF OFFICE", "question": "Outline three principles of a good organization", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- The principle of authority: Responsibility for results should correspond with manager's authority and influence.     - The principle of span of control: Span of control refers to span of supervision or management or authority and responsibility. It stands for the number of subordinates seeking the direction, guidance and supervision from their immediate superior.     - The principle of balance: Balance in organisation structure does not stand for equal emphasis on size and number of people working; it does not mean equality per se. There should be balance from the point view of overall effectiveness.", "marks": "6", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>2>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE CORRESPONDENCE : MEANING OF OFFICE CORRESPONDENCE", "question": "State three advantages derived from office correspondence", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- The basic purpose of any business letter is to convey information regarding business activities. Information can be transmitted through business letter to customers, suppliers, debtors, government authorities, financial institutions, bank and insurance companies and to any other parties related with the business.     - Memo: It can help maintain the good relationship among boss and subordinates, because the bossing attitude is absent here     - The main objective of memo is to inform the decisions and actions. For this purpose, it shouls be wriiten by higher authority.", "marks": "6", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>2>c>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "COMMUNICATION : METHODS/MEDIA OF COMMUNICATION", "question": "Explan the following methods of payment    - Money order", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "An order for the payment of a specified amount of money, usually issued and payable at a bank or post office.. It remain a trusted financial instrument.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>2>c>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "COMMUNICATION : METHODS/MEDIA OF COMMUNICATION", "question": "Explan the following methods of payment      - Postal order", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "A postal order or postal note is a type of money order usually intended for sending money through the mail. It is purchased at a post office and is payable at another post office to the named recipient.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>2>c>iii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "COMMUNICATION : METHODS/MEDIA OF COMMUNICATION", "question": "Explan the following methods of payment      - cheque", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "A cheque is a written order to a bank to pay a stated sum from the drawer's account, written on a specially printed form. It is also a document that orders a bank to pay a specific amount of money from a person's account to the person in whose name the cheque has been issued.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>2>c>iv", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iv", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "COMMUNICATION : METHODS/MEDIA OF COMMUNICATION", "question": "Explan the following methods of payment      -  standing order", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "A standing order is an instruction a bank account holder gives to their bank to pay a set amount at regular intervals to another's accoun. The instruction is sometimes known as a banker's order.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>3>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE DOCUMENTS : MEANING OF OFFICE DOCUMENT", "question": "What is debit note?", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "A debit note is a document used by a vendor to inform the buyer of current debt obligations, or a document created by a buyer when returning goods received on credit. The debit note can provide information regarding an upcoming invoice or serve as a reminder for funds currenlty due.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>3>b>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE DOCUMENTS : USES", "question": "-Use the information to answer questions beow  Lily & Co Ltd supplied some goods to Timex Enterprise after the order had been paid for. The buyer discovered after receiving the goods that quantities of some goods did not tally with the amount paid. He also found out that they were not accompained by any document.    - which document should have accompanied the goods?", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Delivery note", "marks": "1", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>3>b>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE DOCUMENTS : USES", "question": "-Use the information to answer questions beow  Lily & Co Ltd supplied some goods to Timex Enterprise after the order had been paid for. The buyer discovered after receiving the goods that quantities of some goods did not tally with the amount paid. He also found out that they were not accompained by any document.      - Outline four items the document named in 3(b)(i) would contain", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Data identifying the seller and buyer     - Reference to the invoice     - Number and description of the products     - Date of issue of the document and date of delivery of the goods     - Name, signature and stamp of the purchaser, accepting delivery of the goods in good condition", "marks": "8", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>3>c>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE DOCUMENTS : USES", "question": "-Use the information to answer questions beow  Lily & Co Ltd supplied some goods to Timex Enterprise after the order had been paid for. The buyer discovered after receiving the goods that quantities of some goods did not tally with the amount paid. He also found out that they were not accompained by any document.    - Identify the document Timex Enterprise would receive from Lily & Co Ltd that the goods supplied were not complete", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Purchase order", "marks": "1", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>3>c>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "OFFICE DOCUMENTS : USES", "question": "-Use the information to answer questions beow  Lily & Co Ltd supplied some goods to Timex Enterprise after the order had been paid for. The buyer discovered after receiving the goods that quantities of some goods did not tally with the amount paid. He also found out that they were not accompained by any document.      Outline four items the document identified in 3(b)(i) would contain", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Delivery date: It shows when the goods will be delivered i.e the time and date when the goods will be delivered.     - Delivery location: It shows how where the goods will be delivered by the seller.     - Products or services being purchased: It shows the quantity of goods purcahsed by the buyer     - Price per unit: It shows the price of quantity of each goods purchased by the buyer.", "marks": "8", "difficulty": "3"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>4>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "MEETINGS : WRITING THE MINUTES", "question": "List eight features of minutes of meeting of an organization", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Record attendance   - Decisions, actions and owners   - Report and relevant files   - Use a structured format   - Distributes the minutes   - Name of minute taker   - Names of persons   - Name of the group holding the meeting   - Kind of meeting", "marks": "8", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>4>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "COMMUNICATION : COMMUNICATION SERVICE PROVIDERS", "question": "State six benefit of using Global System for Mobile Communications( GSM)", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- More suitable network with robust features   - No roaming charges on international calls   - Worldwide connectivity and extensive coverage   - SAIC and DAIC techniques use in GSM provide very high transmission quality   - GSM signals don't have any deterioration   - Easy to integrate GSM with other wireless technology such as CDMA and LTE   - It has the ability to use repeaters", "marks": "12", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>5>a>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "Explain the following terms relating to payment of worker:    - salary", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "A salary is the money paid each month by their employer, especially when they are in a profession such as teaching, law or medicine.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>5>a>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "Explain the following terms relating to payment of worker:      - wages", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Wages are form of monetary compensation for employees. They are paid according to the amount of time worked by the employee.", "marks": "1", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>5>a>iii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iii", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "Explain the following terms relating to payment of worker:      - time rate", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Time rates are use when employees are paid for the amount of time they spend at work", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>5>a>iv", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "iv", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "Explain the following terms relating to payment of worker:      piece rate", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Piece rate gives a payment for each item produced. It is therefore the easiest way for a business to ensure that employees are paid for the amount of work done.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>5>a>v", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "v", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "Explain the following terms relating to payment of worker:      commission", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Commission is a service charge assessed by a broker or investment advisor for providing advice or handling purchases or sales of security for a client.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>5>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "THE OFFICE : FUNCTIONS OF OFFICE", "question": "State five importance of ofiice procedure", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- An office procedure reduces then general cost of operation   - It allows for effective training of new staff   - It enhances performance of old staff   - A good office procedure facilitataes better flow of work in the office and between department", "marks": "10", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>6>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "THE RECEPTION : DUTIES", "question": "As a receptionist of a Manufacturing company, outline any five actions you would take to handle a telephone call from a customer", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Be polite: Have a standard greeting and use it each time you pick up the phone.     - Stay organized: Take detailed notes. Pay attention to what time calls came in and write down caller ID. Have the company directory at your fingertips for last transfer.     - Listen carefully; Practice active lsitening. Focus on what the caller is saying and quickly determine where to transfer them to best serve their needs.       - Communicate effectively: Don't mumble, speak too quickly, or sound forlorn. Do not enunciate properly, speak at a conformtable pace,and assist callers with energy and enthusiasm.     - Verify: Take a moment to repeat the caller's number back to him and make sure it's correct. If you are unsure how to spell a caller's name, ask her. confirm the most important details of the call before passing the message along to its intended recipient     - Ask the caller's permission: Before placing someone on hold, ask the caller if it's ok.     - Say thank you: If the caller says they will hold, say than you.", "marks": "10", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>6>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "FILING : STEPS IN FILING", "question": "The clerk at Toppy Tee has been directed to file a new customer's letter. Meanwhile, there is no file in the cabinet that is relevant to the subject matter of the letter.   - Outline five actions the office clerk would take in filling the letter.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Receiving the document; If it is a letter or document that came through the mail, record it in the mail received register and write the date received or date stamp it.     - Action: Forward the letter to the person that has to deal with it.     - Follow up: Check that the letter has been dealt with     - Collecting the lettter; All letters and two copies of the replies must be collected in a filing tray     - Filing: Choose a regular time to file", "marks": "10", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>7>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "FILING : DEFINITION OF FILING", "question": "Explain the term filling?", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Filing means keeping documents in a safe place and being able to find them easily and quickly. The purpose of filing is to locate filed documents easily. They are readily available when needed.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>7>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "REPORT WRITINGS : PARTS OF A REPORT", "question": "List any three parts of an investigative report", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Information to identify the case   - Referral source   - Allegation details", "marks": "3", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2021>7>c", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2021", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "c", "group": "CLOSENESS", "topic": "REPORT WRITINGS : MEANING OR REPORT WRITING", "question": "List and explain five qualities of a formal report.", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "- Suitable title   - Simple   - Promptness   - Comparability   - Consistency     - Suitable title: A suitable title has to be provided to each report according to the nature of the number content     - Simple: A report should be reachable by an ordinary layman and in known language     - Promptness: A report should be prepared and submitted with short span of time or time stipulated by the request letter     - Comparability: Sometimes a report is prepared with some comparative information     - Consistency: A report should be prepared for many years from the same type of information and statistical data.", "marks": "15", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>1>a>i", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "i", "group": "", "topic": "FILING : SYSTEMS OF FILING", "question": "Read the case below carefully and answer the questions that follow    CHALLENGES AT SKJ SERVICES LTD    SKJ Services Ltd is a telecommunication company that offers postal and courier services. The headquarters is located in Abeokuta. Due to high demand of the company's services, the company established branches in other cities of the country.    Each branch of the company keeps the files of its staff and customers. The headquarters in Abeokuta supplies and repairs all office machines and equipment needed by its branches. This has been the practice since its inception.    The air conditioner in the reception at Enugu branch developed some faults beyond repairs. Owing to the severe heat, visitors that call at the office do not feel comfortable; they move in and out of the reception which makes the place very rowdy. Some of the visitors sometimes vented their anger on Mr Charlie for the discomfort in the reception.    Owing to the discomfort experienced by the visitors at the reception, Mr Charlie, the receptionist at the Enugu branch made a request for the supply of a new air conditioner to Mr Ken Ojo, the manager at the branch. However, this request was yet to be approved. Mr Charlie became unhappy and started displaying unprofessional attitude in his duties. For instance, if a visitor without an appointment arrives the office, he would not attend to the visitor. The cause of this unprofessional attitude is as a result of the delay from the headquarters acceding to the request for the supply of a new air conditioner.    Due to this attitude, some customers who felt dissatisfied left the company for other companies with better service delivery.    Identify and explain the filing system adopted by SKJ Services Ltd", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "The filing system adopted by SKJ Services Ltd can be identified as a centralized filing system. In this system, all files related to staff and customers are maintained at the headquarters in Abeokuta, while the branches keep their own records. This centralized approach allows for uniformity in record-keeping and ensures that all branches have access to the same information. However, it can also lead to delays in addressing local issues, as seen in the case of the Enugu branch's air conditioner request. A centralized filing system is beneficial for maintaining consistency and control over documents, but it can hinder responsiveness to immediate needs at branch locations.", "marks": "4", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>1>a>ii", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "ii", "group": "", "topic": "FILING : SYSTEMS OF FILING", "question": "Read the case below carefully and answer the questions that follow    CHALLENGES AT SKJ SERVICES LTD    SKJ Services Ltd is a telecommunication company that offers postal and courier services. The headquarters is located in Abeokuta. Due to high demand of the company's services, the company established branches in other cities of the country.    Each branch of the company keeps the files of its staff and customers. The headquarters in Abeokuta supplies and repairs all office machines and equipment needed by its branches. This has been the practice since its inception.    The air conditioner in the reception at Enugu branch developed some faults beyond repairs. Owing to the severe heat, visitors that call at the office do not feel comfortable; they move in and out of the reception which makes the place very rowdy. Some of the visitors sometimes vented their anger on Mr Charlie for the discomfort in the reception.    Owing to the discomfort experienced by the visitors at the reception, Mr Charlie, the receptionist at the Enugu branch made a request for the supply of a new air conditioner to Mr Ken Ojo, the manager at the branch. However, this request was yet to be approved. Mr Charlie became unhappy and started displaying unprofessional attitude in his duties. For instance, if a visitor without an appointment arrives the office, he would not attend to the visitor. The cause of this unprofessional attitude is as a result of the delay from the headquarters acceding to the request for the supply of a new air conditioner.    Due to this attitude, some customers who felt dissatisfied left the company for other companies with better service delivery.    State three advantages of the identified filing system in 1(a)(i)", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Three advantages of a centralized filing system include: 1. Consistency: A centralized filing system ensures that all branches follow the same procedures and standards for record-keeping, which helps maintain uniformity across the organization. 2. Easier Access to Information: Centralized systems allow for easier retrieval of information, as all records are stored in one location. This can facilitate better decision-making and quicker responses to inquiries. 3. Improved Security: With a centralized system, it is easier to implement security measures to protect sensitive information, as there are fewer locations to monitor compared to a decentralized system where files are scattered across multiple branches.", "marks": "6", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>1>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "", "topic": "OFFICE DOCUMENTS : MEANING OF OFFICE DOCUMENT", "question": "Read the case below carefully and answer the questions that follow    CHALLENGES AT SKJ SERVICES LTD    SKJ Services Ltd is a telecommunication company that offers postal and courier services. The headquarters is located in Abeokuta. Due to high demand of the company's services, the company established branches in other cities of the country.    Each branch of the company keeps the files of its staff and customers. The headquarters in Abeokuta supplies and repairs all office machines and equipment needed by its branches. This has been the practice since its inception.    The air conditioner in the reception at Enugu branch developed some faults beyond repairs. Owing to the severe heat, visitors that call at the office do not feel comfortable; they move in and out of the reception which makes the place very rowdy. Some of the visitors sometimes vented their anger on Mr Charlie for the discomfort in the reception.    Owing to the discomfort experienced by the visitors at the reception, Mr Charlie, the receptionist at the Enugu branch made a request for the supply of a new air conditioner to Mr Ken Ojo, the manager at the branch. However, this request was yet to be approved. Mr Charlie became unhappy and started displaying unprofessional attitude in his duties. For instance, if a visitor without an appointment arrives the office, he would not attend to the visitor. The cause of this unprofessional attitude is as a result of the delay from the headquarters acceding to the request for the supply of a new air conditioner.    Due to this attitude, some customers who felt dissatisfied left the company for other companies with better service delivery.    Identify the office document used by Mr. Ken Ojo to request for the supply of air conditioner from the headquarters of SKJ Services Ltd", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "The office document used by Mr. Ken Ojo to request the supply of an air conditioner from the headquarters of SKJ Services Ltd is a 'memo' or 'memorandum'. A memo is a written message used in business communication to convey information or requests within an organization. It is typically brief and to the point, making it an effective way to communicate requests or updates to colleagues or superiors.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>1>c", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "c", "group": "", "topic": "THE RECEPTION : DUTIES", "question": "Read the case below carefully and answer the questions that follow    CHALLENGES AT SKJ SERVICES LTD    SKJ Services Ltd is a telecommunication company that offers postal and courier services. The headquarters is located in Abeokuta. Due to high demand of the company's services, the company established branches in other cities of the country.    Each branch of the company keeps the files of its staff and customers. The headquarters in Abeokuta supplies and repairs all office machines and equipment needed by its branches. This has been the practice since its inception.    The air conditioner in the reception at Enugu branch developed some faults beyond repairs. Owing to the severe heat, visitors that call at the office do not feel comfortable; they move in and out of the reception which makes the place very rowdy. Some of the visitors sometimes vented their anger on Mr Charlie for the discomfort in the reception.    Owing to the discomfort experienced by the visitors at the reception, Mr Charlie, the receptionist at the Enugu branch made a request for the supply of a new air conditioner to Mr Ken Ojo, the manager at the branch. However, this request was yet to be approved. Mr Charlie became unhappy and started displaying unprofessional attitude in his duties. For instance, if a visitor without an appointment arrives the office, he would not attend to the visitor. The cause of this unprofessional attitude is as a result of the delay from the headquarters acceding to the request for the supply of a new air conditioner.    Due to this attitude, some customers who felt dissatisfied left the company for other companies with better service delivery.    Outline four attributes that should be possessed by Mr Charlie ot be effective in his choice", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Four attributes that Mr. Charlie should possess to be effective in his role as a receptionist include: 1. Professionalism: Mr. Charlie should maintain a professional demeanor, even in challenging situations, to ensure that visitors feel welcomed and valued. 2. Communication Skills: Effective communication is crucial for a receptionist. Mr. Charlie should be able to convey information clearly and listen to visitors' needs attentively. 3. Patience: Dealing with visitors, especially those without appointments, requires patience. Mr. Charlie should be able to handle such situations calmly and courteously. 4. Problem-Solving Skills: Mr. Charlie should be able to think on his feet and find solutions to issues that arise, such as managing visitor expectations when the office is busy or when equipment is malfunctioning.", "marks": "4", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>1>d", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "d", "group": "", "topic": "THE RECEPTION : DUTIES", "question": "Read the case below carefully and answer the questions that follow    CHALLENGES AT SKJ SERVICES LTD    SKJ Services Ltd is a telecommunication company that offers postal and courier services. The headquarters is located in Abeokuta. Due to high demand of the company's services, the company established branches in other cities of the country.    Each branch of the company keeps the files of its staff and customers. The headquarters in Abeokuta supplies and repairs all office machines and equipment needed by its branches. This has been the practice since its inception.    The air conditioner in the reception at Enugu branch developed some faults beyond repairs. Owing to the severe heat, visitors that call at the office do not feel comfortable; they move in and out of the reception which makes the place very rowdy. Some of the visitors sometimes vented their anger on Mr Charlie for the discomfort in the reception.    Owing to the discomfort experienced by the visitors at the reception, Mr Charlie, the receptionist at the Enugu branch made a request for the supply of a new air conditioner to Mr Ken Ojo, the manager at the branch. However, this request was yet to be approved. Mr Charlie became unhappy and started displaying unprofessional attitude in his duties. For instance, if a visitor without an appointment arrives the office, he would not attend to the visitor. The cause of this unprofessional attitude is as a result of the delay from the headquarters acceding to the request for the supply of a new air conditioner.    Due to this attitude, some customers who felt dissatisfied left the company for other companies with better service delivery.    Suggest two ways that Mr Charlie would have handled visitors without appointments at SKJ Services Ltd", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Two ways that Mr. Charlie could have handled visitors without appointments at SKJ Services Ltd include: 1. Offering to Schedule an Appointment: Mr. Charlie could politely inform the visitor that they do not have an appointment but offer to schedule one for them at the earliest convenience. This shows respect for the visitor's time and needs while maintaining the office's appointment system. 2. Providing Basic Assistance: If possible, Mr. Charlie could offer to assist the visitor with basic inquiries or direct them to the appropriate resources while they wait for an appointment. This approach can help alleviate frustration and improve the visitor's experience, even if they cannot be seen immediately.", "marks": "4", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>2>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "", "topic": "REPORT WRITINGS : MEANING OR REPORT WRITING", "question": "What is a report?", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "A report is a structured document that presents information in an organized format for a specific audience and purpose. Reports are often used in business, academia, and government to convey findings, analyses, and recommendations based on research or investigation. They typically include sections such as an introduction, methodology, findings, conclusions, and recommendations. The purpose of a report is to inform decision-making, provide evidence for actions, and communicate results effectively.", "marks": "3", "difficulty": "1"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>2>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "", "topic": "REPORT WRITINGS : PARTS OF A REPORT", "question": "List seven parts of a formal report", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "A formal report typically consists of the following seven parts: 1. Title Page: This includes the title of the report, the author's name, and the date of publication. 2. Table of Contents: A list of the sections and subsections of the report along with their page numbers. 3. Executive Summary: A brief overview of the report's contents, including the main findings and recommendations. 4. Introduction: This section outlines the purpose of the report, the problem being addressed, and the scope of the report. 5. Methodology: A description of the methods used to gather data and conduct research. 6. Findings: The main body of the report where the data and information are presented and analyzed. 7. Conclusion and Recommendations: A summary of the findings and suggestions for action based on the analysis.", "marks": "7", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>2>c", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "c", "group": "", "topic": "REPORT WRITINGS : IMPORTANCE OF REPORT WRITING", "question": "Outline five importance of reports to an organization", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Reports are important to an organization for several reasons: 1. Decision-Making: Reports provide critical information that helps management make informed decisions. 2. Accountability: They serve as a record of activities and outcomes, ensuring that individuals and departments are accountable for their performance. 3. Communication: Reports facilitate communication within the organization and with external stakeholders, ensuring that everyone is informed about key issues and developments. 4. Performance Evaluation: They help in assessing the effectiveness of strategies and operations, allowing for adjustments and improvements. 5. Compliance: Reports often fulfill legal and regulatory requirements, ensuring that the organization adheres to necessary standards and practices.", "marks": "10", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>3>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "", "topic": "THE OFFICE : FUNCTIONS OF OFFICE", "question": "Oseh & Co. is into the production of biscuits and has just opened a new branch in Abuja in order to meet the demands of its customers. Only the managers at Oseh & Co. have office to themselves.    Identify the type of office given to the managers at Oseh & Co", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "The type of office given to the managers at Oseh & Co. is known as a 'private office' or 'executive office.' This type of office is designed to provide managers with a dedicated space that offers privacy and a conducive environment for focused work. Private offices are typically equipped with necessary amenities and resources that allow managers to perform their duties effectively without distractions.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>3>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "", "topic": "THE OFFICE : FUNCTIONS OF OFFICE", "question": "Oseh & Co. is into the production of biscuits and has just opened a new branch in Abuja in order to meet the demands of its customers. Only the managers at Oseh & Co. have office to themselves.    State three advantage of the identified office in 3(a)", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "The advantages of having a private office for managers at Oseh & Co. include: 1. Enhanced Privacy: Managers can conduct confidential discussions and work without interruptions, which is crucial for sensitive decision-making. 2. Increased Productivity: A private office allows for fewer distractions, enabling managers to focus better on their tasks and responsibilities. 3. Professional Environment: Having a dedicated office space enhances the professional image of the managers, which can positively influence clients and employees alike.", "marks": "6", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>3>c", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "c", "group": "", "topic": "THE OFFICE : FUNCTIONS OF OFFICE", "question": "Oseh & Co. is into the production of biscuits and has just opened a new branch in Abuja in order to meet the demands of its customers. Only the managers at Oseh & Co. have office to themselves.    List four office staff that could be found in the Abuja branch of the company", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "In the Abuja branch of Oseh & Co., the following four office staff could be found: 1. Administrative Assistant - responsible for managing office tasks and supporting the managers. 2. Receptionist - the first point of contact for visitors and responsible for handling incoming calls. 3. Accounts Clerk - manages financial records and transactions. 4. Human Resources Officer - handles employee-related functions such as recruitment and staff welfare.", "marks": "4", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>3>d", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "d", "group": "", "topic": "THE OFFICE : FUNCTIONS OF OFFICE", "question": "Oseh & Co. is into the production of biscuits and has just opened a new branch in Abuja in order to meet the demands of its customers. Only the managers at Oseh & Co. have office to themselves.    State four functions of the office at Abuja branch of the company", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "The four functions of the office at the Abuja branch of Oseh & Co. include: 1. Communication - facilitating effective communication within the organization and with external stakeholders. 2. Record Keeping - maintaining accurate records of transactions, correspondence, and other important documents. 3. Coordination - ensuring that different departments and staff work together efficiently to meet company goals. 4. Support Services - providing necessary support to managers and staff, including administrative and logistical assistance.", "marks": "8", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>4>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "", "topic": "INFORMATION : USES", "question": "List four devices for sharing information", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Four devices for sharing information include: 1. Email - a digital communication tool that allows users to send messages and documents quickly. 2. Instant Messaging Apps - platforms like Slack or Microsoft Teams that enable real-time communication among team members. 3. Cloud Storage Services - such as Google Drive or Dropbox, which allow users to store and share files online. 4. Video Conferencing Tools - like Zoom or Skype, which facilitate virtual meetings and discussions.", "marks": "4", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>4>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "", "topic": "THE OFFICE : LAYOUT OF AN OFFICE", "question": "Highlight four sections in an office", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Four sections in an office typically include: 1. Reception Area - where visitors are greeted and directed. 2. Administrative Section - where administrative tasks are performed, often including offices for administrative staff. 3. Finance Department - responsible for managing the company's financial activities. 4. Human Resources Section - focused on employee management and welfare.", "marks": "4", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>4>c", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "c", "group": "", "topic": "INFORMATION : DEFINITIONS", "question": "List and explain four qualities of good information", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Four qualities of good information are: 1. Accuracy - information must be correct and free from errors to be reliable. 2. Timeliness - information should be provided in a timely manner to be relevant for decision-making. 3. Relevance - the information must be pertinent to the needs of the users. 4. Clarity - information should be presented in a clear and understandable manner to avoid confusion.", "marks": "12", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>5>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "Explain the term span of control", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "The term 'span of control' refers to the number of subordinates that a manager or supervisor can effectively oversee. It is a crucial concept in organizational structure and management, as it influences the efficiency and effectiveness of communication, decision-making, and overall management. A narrow span of control means that a manager supervises a small number of employees, allowing for closer supervision and more direct communication. Conversely, a wide span of control means that a manager oversees a larger number of employees, which can lead to less direct supervision but may also encourage greater autonomy among employees. The optimal span of control depends on various factors, including the nature of the work, the skills of the employees, and the management style of the supervisor.", "marks": "2", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>5>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "State four factors tha determines span of control", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Four factors that determine the span of control include: 1. Nature of the Work: If the tasks are complex and require close supervision, a narrower span of control is preferable. 2. Employee Skills: Highly skilled and experienced employees may require less supervision, allowing for a wider span of control. 3. Management Style: A more hands-on management style may necessitate a narrower span, while a more delegative style can accommodate a wider span. 4. Geographic Dispersion: If employees are spread out over a large area, it may be challenging for a manager to maintain a wide span of control effectively.", "marks": "8", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>5>c", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "c", "group": "", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "Outline five functions of delegation of authority", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Five functions of delegation of authority include: 1. Empowerment: Delegation empowers employees by giving them the authority to make decisions and take actions within their roles. 2. Skill Development: It provides opportunities for employees to develop their skills and gain experience in decision-making and leadership. 3. Efficiency: Delegation allows managers to focus on higher-level tasks by distributing routine tasks among subordinates, leading to increased organizational efficiency. 4. Motivation: When employees are entrusted with responsibilities, it can enhance their motivation and job satisfaction, as they feel valued and trusted. 5. Accountability: Delegation clarifies accountability, as employees understand their responsibilities and the expectations associated with their roles.", "marks": "10", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>6", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "6", "group": "", "topic": "CASH BOOK", "question": "Enter the following expenses of Okon & Sons transactions for the month of March, 2022 into the petty cash book:    1/3 Cash received  #20001/3 Purchase of stamps #20002/3 Stationeries #50005/3 Transport to bank #100010/3 Cartridge #300012/3 Office pins #100014/3 Recharge card #200020/3 Transport to post office #100021/3 Recharge card #2000", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Okon & Sons   Petty Cash Book  | Date   | Description                     | Amount  |  |--------|---------------------------------|---------|  | 1/3    | Cash received                   | #2000   |  | 1/3    | Purchase of stamps              | #2000   |  | 2/3    | Stationeries                    | #5000   |  | 5/3    | Transport to bank               | #1000   |  | 10/3   | Cartridge                       | #3000   |  | 12/3   | Office pins                     | #1000   |  | 14/3   | Recharge card                   | #2000   |  | 20/3   | Transport to post office        | #1000   |  | 21/3   | Recharge card                   | #2000   |", "marks": "20", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>7>a", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "a", "group": "", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "Explain the concept organizational chart", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "An organizational chart is a visual representation of the structure of an organization. It outlines the relationships and relative ranks of its parts and positions/jobs. The chart typically displays the hierarchy of the organization, showing how different roles and departments are interconnected. Organizational charts can vary in complexity, from simple structures with few levels of management to more complex diagrams that include multiple departments and teams. They serve several purposes, including clarifying reporting relationships, improving communication, and aiding in the understanding of the organization's structure. Additionally, they can help identify areas for improvement in workflow and efficiency.", "marks": "3", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>7>b", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "b", "group": "", "topic": "DEPARTMENTS IN AN ORGANIZATION : FUNCTIONS OF EACH DEPARTMENT", "question": "Identify and explain three types of organizational chart", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Organizational charts are visual representations of the structure of an organization, showing the relationships and relative ranks of its parts and positions/jobs. There are several types of organizational charts, but three common types are: 1. Hierarchical Organizational Chart: This is the most common type of organizational chart. It displays the structure of an organization in a top-down format, with the highest-ranking individuals at the top and lower-ranking individuals beneath them. This type of chart clearly shows the chain of command and the reporting relationships within the organization. 2. Matrix Organizational Chart: In a matrix organizational chart, employees have dual reporting relationships - generally to both a functional manager and a product manager. This type of chart is useful in organizations that work on multiple projects simultaneously, as it allows for more flexibility and collaboration across different departments. 3. Flat Organizational Chart: A flat organizational chart has few or no levels of middle management between staff and executives. This type of structure is often used in startups and small businesses, where the emphasis is on employee autonomy and collaboration. Flat organizational charts can lead to faster decision-making and a more agile organization, but they may also result in confusion regarding roles and responsibilities. Each type of organizational chart serves a different purpose and can be used to communicate the structure and dynamics of an organization effectively.", "marks": "9", "difficulty": "2"}, {"id": "theory>Office Practice>2025>7>c", "subject": "Office Practice", "year": "2025", "type": "Theory", "sub_label": "c", "group": "", "topic": "MAILS : TYPES OF MAILS", "question": "Identify and explain the two classification of mail", "images": [], "marking_scheme": "Mail can be classified into two main categories: 1. Internal Mail: This type of mail is used for communication within an organization. It includes memos, interoffice correspondence, and any other documents that are circulated among employees or departments. Internal mail is typically handled through internal mail systems, which may include physical delivery by office staff or electronic communication via email. The primary purpose of internal mail is to facilitate communication and information sharing among employees. 2. External Mail: External mail refers to any correspondence that is sent outside of the organization. This includes letters, packages, and documents sent to clients, suppliers, or other external parties. External mail is usually processed through postal services or courier companies. It is important for organizations to manage external mail effectively, as it often represents the organization's communication with the outside world and can impact its reputation. Both types of mail play crucial roles in the functioning of an organization, ensuring that information flows smoothly both internally and externally.", "marks": "8", "difficulty": "2"}];